parameters:
Would you like to see the event? The new attraction is
officially introduced.

\nc<Saki>Lately, my achievements have been somewhat lacking. Is there
any good activity available?

\nc<Senpai>Oh, already feeling monotonous? But I'm impressed that
you're concerned about your performance.
\bustMsgExp[1, 2]\nc<Saki>What kind of person did you think I was, Senpai...?

\nc<Senpai>A good activity, huh... Those aren't something you can
easily get. Normally, a veteran succubus like me would take
them all.

\nc<Senpai>You should know that much by now, Saki. But you're in luck.
There's just the right activity for you.
\bustMsgExp[1, 4]\nc<Saki>Really? What kind of activity is it??

\bustMsgExp[2, 0]\nc<Senpai>Do you remember the new type of attraction you tested the
other day?

\bustMsgExp[1, 1]\nc<Saki>Eh, you don't mean... that one where I was trapped between
walls and played with...?

\nc<Senpai>Yes, that one. It's been officially adopted as an
attraction.

\bustMsgExp[1, 0]\nc<Saki>I see. So it ended up being adopted. But if it's the same as
last time...

\bustMsgExp[2, 1]\nc<Senpai>What are you talking about? We wouldn't release the test
version as is, right?
\nc<Saki>I see. So it has been improved accordingly?

\bustMsgExp[2, 0]\nc<Senpai>Yes. Especially this time, it's quite different from the
test version, so I think you'll be surprised. What will you
do?

\bustMsgExp[1, 2]\nc<Saki>It's a tough decision. The last one was quite intense, but
the results were good...

\nc<Senpai>Right? It's very efficient, so it seems we've got quite a
few reservations already. If you hesitate, someone else
might take your spot...
\bustMsgExp[1, 1]\nc<Saki>What, really? In that case... I'll give it another try!

\bustMsgExp[2, 3]\nc<Senpai>Hehe, Saki is so easily swayed, which makes you easy to
handle.
\bustMsgExp[2, 0]\nc<Senpai>It's nothing. Well then, off you go.

\bustMsgExp[1, 3]\nc<Saki>If it's been improved from last time, maybe I can work a bit
more comfortably?
